cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the optimization of content distribution over the network using Information-Centric Networking (ICN) architectures. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper proposes a new distributed forwarding and caching algorithm. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses the design of algorithms for joint dynamic forwarding and caching. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as the paper discusses the demand for content objects and their distribution over the network. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper characterizes the stability region of the modified virtual plane with VIP scaling.
